Description:
DELIGHTFUL WATERFRONT OPPORTUNITY
Here is a fabulous opportunity to enter the waterfront market of the tightly held Corinella foreshore. Being offered for the first time since 1989, this well established family home is situated on a double block of approximately 1025 square metres.
The home is well built and provides two large living zones, both with big windows out to the front, room for lounges and dining and both having wood heating. The original kitchen is still in place and offers ample room for entertaining. Stepping down the central hallway is the large laundry with door to the rear and ample storage, separate toilet, main bathroom with spa bath and separate shower. Three good sized bedrooms service the home and have lovely outlooks to the foreshore and gardens.
This property does not disappoint, with lovely outlooks on the grounds as well as out to Westernport. Externally this home offers mature fruit trees, garden beds and paths, along with a garden shed, pond, huge boat shed with plenty of room for the workshop, as well as a large double carport and off street parking.
Don't miss your opportunity, contact the team at Alex Scott & Staff Bass Valley today to arrange your inspection!

Description:
Final Stage - Eastern Shores
Lot 32 Yaringa Close, Elevated lot of 968 m2
Eastern Shores Estate last and FINAL land release is underway with Titles expected early 2018. The land enjoys views towards the sea and the woodland nature reserve next to the estate. Land sizes vary and the land whilst mostly flat has some elevated lots which will capture views. This is the final stage of land release in Grantville at present so get in early to secure your lot. Eastern Shores is located minutes stroll away from all the shops and services in Grantville which include a Post Office, Newsagency, Council Offices, Medical Centre, Ambulance station and Chemist. There are a number of Cafes and fast food outlets and a Bakery. Grantville is approx. 20 mins from San Remo, 30 mins from Wonthaggi and Cowes and approx. 35 mins from Cranbourne and Pakenham. There is an excellent new Early Childhood campus beside the popular Bass Valley Primary School and there are multiple Secondary School options in the locality. A V- Line Bus runs regularly to Melbourne and beyond into Gippsland. The township is growing rapidly but land is running out just as fast!
Deposit of $500 is due upon signing contracts with the balance of 10% deposit within 21 days. The balance will be due within 14 days of the Titles being issued by the Land Titles office.
Contact Liz Leahy for more information on 0487 022 099

Description:
ONLY METRES TO THE ESPLANADE !!!!
When location counts. Located in the sought after area near Corinella's popular 24 hour boat ramp and jetty, is this attractive 500 sq.m. coastal block, situated in a quaint estate. Take a stroll along the scenic coastal walking track or just take the family for a picnic at the foreshore. Build a two-storey home to capture some water views. Corinella is known for its great fishing and is only approx. 110 kms easy commute with dual lane highway. Approx. 7 mins is a small group of shops with permanent doctor, chemist, bank, ambulance depot and cafes, local wineries and Phillip Island and major shopping centre approx. 25 mins.

Description:
LAVISH GARDEN ON A LARGE BLOCK IN LANG LANG
This wonderful brick family home situated in a friendly neighbourhood presents great value for money! Positioned on a large 1132 m2 approx. block featuring a beautifully presented front and rear mature garden with an oversized paved patio area and a large lockable shed containing power and a concrete floor. The lovely brick paved driveway leads up to the double car garage which has rear access into the house, the paving also leads all the way up to the shed.
The stunning garden has a watering system installed and can be attached to the tanks on the property or mains water.
As you enter the home you are greeted by high ceilings and a wide entrance with the large lounge room to the right featuring an exposed brick arch way and wall with the stunning original fire place. This home also includes gas ducted heating throughout, a free standing wood heater and a split system! The master bedroom is a great size with a walk in robe and ensuite, while the two other bedrooms feature built in robes.
Large kitchen with beautiful timber cabinetry and exceptional bench space! Opens up into the formal dining area and another family meals/seating area which has sliding door access out to the patio.
This home is a must see and has been kept in immaculate condition. It is ready for the next family to continue making memories!
Please contact the friendly team at Alex Scott & Staff Bass Valley today to arrange your inspection!

Address: Lots R 1, 2 & 6, Coast Road French Island VIC 3921
Description:
Substantial parcel of over 400 acres in 3 titles (1 with house)
Offered in one line (Vendors preference) or available separately - all with new fencing.
Feasibility study for wind farm available. Includes weather monitoring equipment on R 2.
Secluded holding in the North West corner of the Island (north of Bullock Road) with one recently rebuilt 2 bdrm home, several small shacks, a private beach, boat mooring, heritage features, disused air strip and more. Currently raising sheep, this flexible farm holding is well fenced with ample water from well formed dams and an upgraded drainage system. Total area on titles is approx 413 acres with approx 50% usable for pasture and the balance protected native bush land. Meteorological measurements have been taken to prove up feasibility of wind farm connected by cable to mainland. Estimates available upon request. Weather station still in situ and can be included in sale by negotiation.
Each property has following attributes:-
Lot R – 1 Coast Road
"Mawsons Shacks" – The north west corner of the Island. Approx. 65.86 ha (162 acres) with foreshore frontage to north and west boundaries, northerly sea views and fully fenced with private driveway access off Coast Road. Some areas cleared for grazing, 2 dams and extensive drainage works. Building permit available STGA.
Lot R – 2 No. 1199 Coast Road
Superb sea views to the north and foreshore frontage. Approx. 51 ha (125 acres) with some areas cleared for grazing with suitable building envelopes, 3 dams and yards. Building permit available STGA.
Lot R – 6 No. 1154 Coast Road
L shaped parcel straddling Coast Road. Approx. 49.7 ha (122 acres) with recently renovated 2-bedroom dwelling. Excellent shedding and near new fencing, 5 dams and potential for landing strip.
Expressions of Interest Closing Friday 14th December at 5:00pm
Terms 10% Deposit Balance 60 Days Vacant Possession.
Contact Phil Bock on 0438 497 715 to inspect

Description:
Seaside Escape - Rural Atmosphere
This remarkable renovated property gives you that highly sought-after but seldom found..... best of both worlds! With its panoramic views taking in the rural setting with rolling hills scattered with trees which lifts to the horizon of the blue sparkling waters of the bay - perfection!
Set on an acre of land ( 4009m2 ) you will feel at ease the moment you make you way down the drive past the electric gates and enter your very own paradise. Once inside the home on the ground level you are greeted with a generous open living area with its own wood fired heater for those cool winter nights, three bedrooms all with built in robes serviced by a modern bathroom plus a functional laundry with enough storage for all your needs.
Upstairs you will be instantly taken back with the elevated setting that immediately draws your eyes to the water and sense of space and freedom that comes with it. Comfort is never far from reach with a smart floor plan that includes the master bedroom complete with ensuite and walk-in robe adjacent a separate lounge room that flows into the main hub of the home being the kitchen and meals area. Your kitchen will let you cook up a storm with more than enough bench and cupboard space while taking in the idyllic setting of the huge spotted gum decking that wraps around the home to take in the best possible vantage points while still allowing access from an external staircase that complete this impressive property.
With a chook shed to keep your daily breakfast in check, together with a large garage to keep everything secure and room for the kids to ride their motorbikes or for that pony they have been asking for nonstop! This property has something for everyone, if you want the perfect weekend getaway or take up a permanent residence you can't drive past without seeing why 56 Acacia is your next place to call home. The photos are spectacular, but seeing it in person will do it the justice it truly deserves. See you soon.

**To book an appointment to view this property, please click on the "Request an inspection" button and register your details and we will instantly respond to you with available inspection times. Description:
ONE ACRE BUSH BLOCK OPPOSITE FORESHORE
THIS COULD BE IT!
A remote affordable one acre bush block located opposite foreshore reserve in North West corner of the Island.
Road reserve on two sides with long frontage to Bullock Road.
Reasonable road access approx 500 meters back off Coast Road and about 10 kilometers from ferry terminal.
A truly secluded spot with near new fencing on two sides with gate in North West corner.
Planning permit available for single dwelling (STGA) and only 1 acre !

Escape from the crowd to your own private secluded bush hideaway.
Perfect for that hidden away holiday shack or camping spot at a price almost anyone can afford.
French Island is around 70% national park and is totally off grid. No council so no rates to pay.

ENDURING CHARM, ENTICING STYLE
The captivating facade of this single level period residence provides an appealing first impression that is matched by the interior that has been comprehensively renovated home to deliver a stunning provincial domain, perfectly situated near Corinella foreshore and walking tracks.
Behind the charming exterior, contemporary themes are highlighted by timber floors and stylish finishes, two bright bedrooms one with built in robe, a stylish bathroom with classic New York black & white style that flows off the master bedroom.
The timber floors extend through an inviting dining area and versatile open plan living, superbly appointed provincial style kitchen, and a retreat bedroom or sunroom opening to an enclosed private deck area.
The home retains the charm of the past while offering a lot for the future and overlooking private romantic gardens of 800m approx.
96 Smythe Street offers extraordinary lifestyle in one of Corinella’s most renowned pockets.
Daniel & Tamara from @realty Bass Coast have the pleasure of presenting this magnificent property in Corinella.

Description:
Quiet Coastal Living
Set on a substantial 504sqm (approx.) block, sits this move-in ready 3 bedroom, 2 bathroom home with stunning water views. With upstairs and downstairs living zones, multiple outdoor entertaining, and manicured gardens this home is truly a move in and enjoy with nothing left to do.
Downstairs you're greeted by a spacious entry, leading into a formal lounge. 3 bedrooms all on the ground floor - master with walk-in robe and ensuite with large double shower, remaining bedrooms complemented by a bright and spacious family bathroom and equipped with built-in robes.
Upstairs is bright and spacious and is the heart of this home, with second living area, separate dining and open-plan kitchen with large island bench - perfect for social entertaining. The kitchen consists of 900mm free-standing stainless steel stove, dishwasher, and plentiful cabinetry. Spectacular water views set the scene for meals on the rear deck, entertaining friends or just relaxing with a book and watching the sunset over the water.
Outside is an established rear yard, private deck off the master suite, garden shed plus substantial 4 bay carport with large gated access. Perfect for storing a boat and also doubles as an extensive outdoor entertaining area.
Other notable features include floating flooring throughout, split system heating and cooling, and quiet street location - all walking distance to Grantville shops, and beach. Inspection will impress

Description:
Beachside Beauty
This Lovely seaside home backs directly onto the Grantville foreshore. Located just over an hours drive from the city this renovated home offers a new kitchen and upgraded vogue style bathroom, floating timber floors & split system air conditioner. There's a large lounge, garage and carport, plenty of room for the boat in this sizable front yard. This property would be an ideal holiday home/weekend retreat or a fantastic opportunity for those looking for a more permanent 'sea change' living with the beach practically at your doorstep.
Call early to arrange an inspection!

Description:
FULLY REFURBISHED ON LARGE BLOCK
All the hard work has been done at this lovely 2 bedroom property including a new deck to the front and rear of the house. It has been fully repainted inside and out, renovated kitchen with new appliances and an upgraded bathroom. The brand new split system keeps the home feeling cosy through the colder months and cool during the warm weather.
The land size is approx. 708m² which features a double carport and huge lockup garage, small shedding to the rear fence and also a garden shed. With plenty of yard space available for pets and/or children to play and all within walking distance to the foreshore!
This house is move in ready and only a short walk to the foreshore!
Please contact the friendly team at Alex Scott & Staff Bass Valley today to arrange your inspection.

Description:
RARE BAYVIEW BEAUTY LIVE THE DREAM.
Don't miss out on this one. This beautiful and very rare parcel of land offers the dream location to build a forever home on in an area destined for explosive growth in coming years. With its' rich black sandy loam soil and a bore for water it could also provide a source of income as a small market garden, fruit or flower farm etc. or a small horse stud.
- 12.5 acres, flat land, highway access, fantastic home site.
- Great location, superb bay views, abuts residential properties.
- Potential future subdivision (STCA), strong tourist growth area.
- Ideal for boutique food-based enterprise, market garden.
- Services available, also has farm water from bore with windmill.
For further information please contact RAY CULLEN on 0429 977313 or 56 295 329

Description:
AMAZING COTTAGE WITH WATER VIEWS - 104 BAYVIEW AVE TENBY POINT
A window of nature in the heart of Tenby Point, this unique property set on 1332m block (approx.) offers a wonderful weekend escape or a permanent home.
Beautifully presented country cottage offers bright & comfortable living. Plenty of living space & generous bedrooms with Bir’s x 2 or possible 3 bedroom could be done. Bathroom, separate toilet, large laundry. Kitchen offers plenty of bench space, family area with wood fire. The home also offers a great deck area down stairs, where you can enjoy the morning sunshine or afternoon sunset, summer and winter.
The upstairs offers two balcony’s one off the master bedroom and the other offers water views and rural views at the rear of the property. There is a large lock up garage and a carport as well.
Only a short walk to the fore shore and Walking Tracks, close to the 24 hour boat jetty, short drive to the Corinella General Store Post Office, close to the Community Centre, Bowls Club, Tennis Courts. You will also be surrounded by all the Bass Coast tourist attractions, Vine Yards, Local Markets, San Remo, Churchill Island Heritage Farm - Philip Island and a lot more.
Please call Tamara or Daniel

Description:
VALUE FOR MONEY!!!!
Coastal 2 storey brick home set on spacious 1,550m2 block near water. Featuring:
Downstairs: Good size entry, 2 bedrooms or 1 bed/plus living, Large kitchen/meals area, Bathroom with shower & toilet.
Upstairs: Family/dining area with polished timber floors, 2nd living area with sliding door to balcony with water views, good size kitchen/meals area, master bedroom with built in robes and door to balcony with water views, family bathroom, office/study nook, laundry & powder room.
There is also two single garages and the block offers so much room for the boat, caravan or extra vehicles as there is plenty of room to build a large shed.
The property is a great size for permanent living or for a couple of families for holidays. Ideally located within walking distance to local shop, community centre, bus stops, tennis courts, playground and hall. Only minutes to 24 hour boat ramp, local primary school and kindergarten, local shops with doctor, chemist, bank and ambulance depot approx.. 7 mins and major shopping centre and Phillip Island approx.. 25 mins. Easy commute to CBD with dual lane highway. There is nothing of this size under $500,000 in Corinella on market, so you will need to be quick.
